FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1779203471
OL,3,CPeston: Starmer ruling out a timetable
OL,4,Cto quit is Olympic level straw-
OL,5,Cclutching
OL,7,FAs a tactic it reminds me of David
OL,8,FCameron vowing he would not quit if he
OL,9,Fwere to lose the Brexit referendum.
OL,11,FWhat transpired was that Cameron
OL,12,Fresigned within hours of being
OL,13,Ftrounced by Johnson, Farage and
OL,14,FCummings.
OL,16,FBut some kind of amour propre is
OL,17,Fpreserved by Starmer's refusal to
OL,18,Fpledge to surrender the throne after
OL,19,Fone more battle.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1779203471
OL,3,CPeston: Starmer ruling out a timetable
OL,4,Cto quit is Olympic level straw-
OL,5,Cclutching
OL,7,FStarmer also says that if someone -
OL,8,Fsay Burnham - were to get the
OL,9,Frequisite 81 nominations and were to
OL,10,Ftrigger a leadership contest, he would
OL,11,Fjoin the fray and fight.
OL,13,FIf he is to be taken at his word, this
OL,14,Fisn't just any old hard ball, but
OL,15,Fdeath-match stuff, with the survival
OL,16,Fof the Labour Party in the frame.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1779203471
OL,3,CPeston: Starmer ruling out a timetable
OL,4,Cto quit is Olympic level straw-
OL,5,Cclutching
OL,7,FAll the important trade union leaders
OL,8,Fwant Starmer to quit, as do a
OL,9,Fsignificant number of Labour MPs (I am
OL,10,Fnot going to say "most" because
OL,11,Freliable data is not available, though
OL,12,Fthe party is conspicuously split).
OL,14,FStarmer is saying "bring it on, if
OL,15,Fyou're hard enough." And we have to
OL,16,Fassume that the Evertonian Burnham
OL,17,Fbelieves he is.
OL,26,@rD@ROUrD@WO]vD@SOUwD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
