PN,31905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1779203471
OL,3,CPeston: Starmer ruling out a timetable
OL,4,Cto quit is Olympic level straw-
OL,5,Cclutching
OL,7,FStarmer's weekend of ruminating about
OL,8,Fhis future at Chequers has not
OL,9,Fintroduced much in the way of self
OL,10,Fdoubt, for all that he is surrounded
OL,11,Fby those who doubt him.
OL,13,FThat is a genius of sorts. Hats off.
OL,15,FMaybe as and when Burnham becomes an
OL,16,FMP again, he will have the revelation
OL,17,Fthat Starmer and Starmerism are a
OL,18,Fwinning combination, despite the
OL,19,Fcontrary evidence of multiple
OL,20,Felections.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1779203471
OL,3,CPeston: Starmer ruling out a timetable
OL,4,Cto quit is Olympic level straw-
OL,5,Cclutching
OL,7,FAnd possibly Streeting, and Rayner,
OL,8,Fand Miliband will suddenly surrender
OL,9,Fany ambition to lead and change the
OL,10,Fcourse adopted by their party.
OL,12,FAnything is possible in these volatile
OL,13,Ftimes. Though I wouldn't attach a high
OL,14,Fprobability to an outcome that
OL,15,Fincreases Starmer's job security.
OL,17,FWhat is highly probable is that if
OL,18,FBurnham wins and Starmer says he ain't
OL,19,Fbudging, we may witness the kind of
OL,20,Fmayhem that could destroy Labour.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
